                <h4>What is the voting age population of Gladwin, Michigan?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Gladwin, Michigan, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 2,091.  The voting age population is 45.1% male and 54.9% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Gladwin, Michigan residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 17.7% of
                        the residents of Gladwin are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Gladwin, Michigan?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Gladwin are 94.5% White, 2.2% Two or more races, 1.7% Asian, 1.3% Black and 0.3% American Indian. Additionally, 2.4% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Gladwin, Michigan residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Gladwin, 22.6% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 35.0%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    18.7% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Gladwin.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Gladwin, Michigan residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 53.9% of
                    Gladwin residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Gladwin, Michigan residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    91.7% of
                    Gladwin residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 14.6%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 6.4%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Gladwin, Michigan residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Gladwin residents aged 5 and older, 2.0% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                0.1% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                1.9% speak an Indo-European language, and
                0.0% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Gladwin, Michigan?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Gladwin is 8.2%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Gladwin, Michigan residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Gladwin, 7.1% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                    <h4>What is the median income in Gladwin, Michigan?</h4>
                    <p>The median household income in Gladwin is $38,258.</p>
                

                
    


                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are owner-occupied in Gladwin, Michigan?</h4>
                <p>
                    In Gladwin, 57.1% of housing units
                    are occupied by their owners.
